
https://realpython.com/learn/start-django/

once installed mysql needs to be accessed using "mysql -u root -p" and filling in the password
Then create the database for django using CREATE DATABASE django_db;

Issues with the mysql_config not being there can be resolved with help:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5178292/pip-install-mysql-python-fails-with-environmenterror-mysql-config-not-found
